        {
          "username": "S K",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "104175272496539325050",
          "user_review_count": 18,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwroGyeQa8fGMpracO1uEmFpb_ZitRwiQdUTtUFAb7gJfBgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Sloppy disorganized team and deeply disappointing, inappropriate, and unprofessional conduct exhibited by the mammogram and ultrasound technicians.\n\nConfirmed my appointment by phone, the Mt Sinai app, and text as well as filled out all the paperwork. Arrived 30 minutes early to an appointment on 12/04 scheduled by my physician on 8/21.\n\nAfter checking in, changing into my gown, and waiting, I was pulled aside by Tatiana, a mammogram technician, in a public space and loudly interrogated about my family history, had my high risk status questioned, and was berated for scheduling a mammogram/ultrasound more often than she personally felt was appropriate. I explained that this testing was ordered by my physician, explained my high risk status, and the changes I had felt since my last exam. Another technician overheard and tried to correct Tatiana, reminding her that any changes warranted further examination (though not the reason for my visit). I was asked to sit back in the waiting area while Tatiana conferred with some authority. She reappeared and without explanation, escorted me for a mammogram where she continued her interrogation about my family history, discounted my high risk status, told me not to worry so much because I am young, breast cancer is rarely dangerous, and my aunt who died because of chemoresistant metastatic breast cancer while still on tamoxifen must\u2019ve ignored symptoms/failed to follow proper protocol because she was a physician.\n\nI was then asked to wait again without any information or details about whether I would be having an ultrasound. After 45 minutes, I was escorted by an ultrasound technician who exhibited similar hostility, behaved as if inconvenienced, and held me personally responsible for being at an appointment scheduled by my physician because she too felt it was too early/often. After the most perfunctory ultrasound with no attempt at being gentle, I was dismissed with the warning that having \u201cimaging this often would be pointless.\u201d\n\nIf there was a scheduling issue, this needed to be addressed internally and preferably in the many weeks prior to a patient\u2019s appointment. It is not the patient\u2019s responsibility to correct nor is it their fault.\n\nI remain deeply disturbed by this experience and urge others to seek care elsewhere. This is not appropriate standard of care.\n\nEdited to add: when I explained that I had a new palpable lump I\u2019d found Tatiana responded that cysts are common in dense breasts (true) and I shouldn\u2019t be worried/should get used to them(dangerous/false).",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21nMFJXc3hhVmd6VFMxTFduTlVkME13ZUVsaWNIYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xd9eefc10e462be80!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmg0RWsxaVgzTS1LWnNUd0MweElicHc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 6 months ago",
